Hello,

I’m mostly a Pathplanner novice and have a few questions on setup and path configuration:

  1. In the robot config menu, I’m inputting the metrics for our robot and the calculated Max Linear Acceleration value continues to stay red unless I enter an artificially large number in the true max drive speed field. Red usually indicates ‘bad’, so I’m wondering what I need to do to correct this. Putting in fake values doesn’t seem like it should be the right approach.

  2. Control lengths - I looked through the docs and couldn’t really find a good description (for me) of what these do. The heading of a waypoint controls the direction of the robot as it passes through that waypoint, but what do the control points do? What impact does changing the length have?

Thanks for any input on this!

With control length, you can adjust the waypoints the robot will pass through on its way to the target and shape its path. This allows for smoother transitions and helps the robot avoid obstacles if there are any in its way.

For example we have this path to avoid collusion to reef.

PKopf:

Isn’t obstacle avoidance done with waypoints on a path?

yes control length helps too you can change path’s curve with control lengths. It can also sometimes be used to create physically accurate paths.

PKopf:

Do control points specify how far the robot will try to stay traveling at a specific heading?

Control points only adjust curve of the path.
